    "created_at": "2019-04-11T16:44:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-04-11T16:46:04Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just a thought for the future/a potential follow-up: Would it be possible to move `OpportunityFire` and `FacingTolerance` to `Armament` (or at least give it overrides)?\r\n\r\nMy line of thinking is that, for example, tracking missiles are much more suited for opportunity fire (at least on non-turreted actors) and wide facing tolerance than a tank cannon, and actors might have both.\r\nThis would also allow to reproduce the behavior of the mammoth tank missile in original TD, which got fired at ground units while turning towards the target.\r\n\r\nIf we do eventually go there, we might even want to refactor `FacingTolerance` to a `ValidFacingRange` that allows to be able to set something like `32, 96` to limit that weapon to fire sideways (think Emperor: BFD Harkonnen Buzzsaw and Flame Tank)."
  }
